args:
The prince and his allies continue their
undercover investigation. They find a murdered
village girl, who was last seen speaking to
Faris shortly before her demise. Faris has since
disappeared and the villagers judge the prince's
group to be responsible, chasing them away.
What did you just say, Pinon?
I suggested that we inform the Church\nthat there's no sealing stone in Paradise\nand head back.
In other words, cut off our investigation?
But Madame used miasma and rewrote\nmemories. You saw it just as well as I.

Do we know for SURE that it was miasma?
What if we just convinced ourselves that's
what it was because of our preconceived
notions?
Are you trying to say that Madame's\nmysterious power really did come to\nher ＂from on high,＂ as she put it?
Whether that's true or not isn't germane to\nthe point, which is that I don't think her\npower stems from a sealing stone.
I patted her down, but she wasn't carrying\none. That's proof positive, above all else.
You may feel that way, but I think it may\nbe premature to decide without question\nthat they are wholly unrelated, dear.
Well then, we just need to prove it for\nsure. But...how do we prove there isn't a\nsealing stone involved in all this?
I think maybe we should investigate a\nlittle more. We could have overlooked\nsomething.
And I'm also curious how Madame was\nable to divine those things about my\nfather and sister.
Surely we can wait long enough to\nmake our call until that's done...right?
Then let's split up and gather information.
You want to know more about Madame?
I've been reflecting on how I doubted her\npower yesterday, see. It's made me want\nto understand her better.
What a laudable thing to say! Ah, but\nMadame is a mystery wrapped inside\na host of enigmas...
You handle much of the village's affairs,\nand even you don't know much about\nMadame?

Lemme think... Oh, hey! I know something
SUPER juicy about her! This is gonna make
you go weak in the knees with surprise,
just you wait!
Well? Are you ready for this?
So chew on this little nugget:\nMadame actually has...a super hot BF!

Like, molten. I bet you could fry an egg
on this guy. I saw him myself! It was just
a little bit before you all came to town,
come to think of it.

Madame was meeting with him in secret
on the outskirts of the village! She handed
him something that looked vaguely gift-
shaped.
This could be a MAJOR scandal! I mean,\nthis is Madame we're talking about—\nthe icon, the legend!
Um, yes. I heard that you've been with\nher the longest.
True. I've been an ironclad believer of hers\nfor a real long time. Since before she even\nfounded Paradise.
She's the founder of the Association of the\nAqueous, which sold water imbued with\nthe most miraculous properties!

(I'm familiar with this particular racket.
The Association was a bunch of frauds
who hawked regular water at premium
prices.)
(And what's more, they invoked the\nGoddess's name for their product...)

But the Church did not ＂approve＂ of Ilia
Springs' crisp, healthy water, so instead
they chucked her in prison! And then the
Association was disbanded. Sad story, no?
Er... You said it. By the way, back when\nMadame led the Association, did she still\nhave the power to rewrite memories?
No. It wasn't until after she finished out\nher prison term that she was granted\nthat incredible ability.
The sham cult, the fancy meeting place,\nthe flashy performance... I've got a pretty\ngood picture of Madame's character now.

She's an attention-craving narcissist
who dreams of being treated like royalty.
And so, she deceives people.
How utterly typical.
But her power is the real deal. Did she\nawaken to it while she was in jail?
Ryszarda... I'm taking points off for that.\nYou don't honestly believe that, do you?
...No. I think Madame's power really\nmust come from a sealing stone.
I don't have a sound argument to back\nit up. Just intuition, sorry to say.
Your ability to think things through\nlogically is lacking, but your keen\nintuition more than makes up for it.
And that's an ability I DON'T have.\nSo have more confidence in yourself.

(But if that IS the case, then we still
don't know how the little scoundrel got
her hands on something as precious as
a sealing stone.)
Faris. Ryszarda.\nDid your investigation bear fruit?
No information about the sealing stones.\nHow about you?
Nothing much. Just...gossip about\nMadame's love life.
Gossip? That doesn't sound very helpful.
What do we do, then?\nPick up the search where we left off?
Little Pi, why don't we get something into\nour bellies before we think about that?
I'm with Gabriel. Running around town\ndoing all that questioning has worked\nup quite an appetite.
You go ahead and eat, then.
Bathroom. I think I can manage it\nwithout an armed escort, thanks.
Pretty crude excuse there, Faris...\nDocking a few points for that one.
Now... I think it'd be best if Pinon and\nthe rest weren't privy to my continued\ninvestigations.
Faris certainly is taking a long time.\nThere's about to be no lunch left to eat.
Did something happen? I'm worried he\nmight've gotten a stomachache and\ncollapsed or something.
Want me to go check on him?
I'm with the neighborhood watch!\nWhat's happened?
A body! A person,\nmangled and murdered!
We were talking to her just a while ago!\nThis is unspeakable...
I saw it! She was talking to that young guy\nyou people were with not long before\nshe turned up dead!
He killed her! There's no doubt about it!
Wait. Faris would never\ndo something like that!
You're going to cover for him, then? Come\nto think of it, you people were nosing\naround asking about Madame as well.
Maybe you're just evil pawns plotting the\ndestruction of Paradise!
In that case, we'll capture you all and\nmake you fess up! Hragh!
Oh, no! I'm sorry.\nI didn't mean to—

Did you see that?! These people are
nothing more than violent brutes! If we
want to protect the peace in our town,
we must put them down here and now!
Put them down! Put them down!\nPut them down! Put them down!
The atmosphere here is...charged, to say\nthe least. They're not going to listen to a\nsingle word we say.
Come on everyone, we need to get\nout of here!
Hey! They ran for it! AFTER THEM!
And find that Faris or whatever his name\nis! Put every last one of them down!
Madame! What are you doing here?
I heard a fracas and came running. Now,\nyou can just leave the punishment of those\noutsiders to my soldiers. Oho ho ho...
